This Goa stay will make you crave a trip soon 🌴
Planned a surprise birthday trip for dad and stayed at Beira Mar Resort - and We didnt expect it to be SO FUN! 

✔️ Spacious garden-view cottages with a seperate shower room and washroom 
✔️ A dreamy beach just a stroll away - 2 min walk literally 
✔️ Huge pool & hearty breakfast spreads every morning 
✔️ Arroz Kitchen's must-try Goan food and multiple cuisine menu 
✔️ In-house spa & kids' play zone for full fam-jam vibes
✔️ Thoughtful staff who even surprised my dad - they had set up an entire surprise before we checked in, SWEETEST 

All this feels like luxury - ut on a budget! 💸

Truly one of the most heartwarming and relaxing stays in South Goa. And it's near the town area, so it's accessible and located in a good spot. 

📌 Save this hidden gem for your next South Goa trip!

Too bored to stay home this monsoon? Here’s your ultimate list of fun things to do in Mumbai - rain and shine! 🌧️✨

1. Sip & Paint at @paintsandfun 🎨
2. Take early morning Rajbhavan tour in south bombay (details online)
3. Smash some stress at @rageroomindia 💥
4. Try your hand at pottery at Dorangos or @studiovida_mumbai in Bandra 🏺
5. Play detective at @mumbai.mysteryrooms or @noescape_mumbai 🔍
6. Get groovy with Jive/Salsa/Dance classes 💃
7. Attend a show at NMACC or a play at Prithvi Theatre 🎭
8. Enjoy an artsy neon splash session at @_neonsplash 🌈
9. Arcade gaming spree at @timezonegames, @thegameranch or @smaaash_official 🕹️
10. Make your own pizza at @sinonnas 🍕
11. Take the stage at a dance/painting session with @small.world 🩰🖌️
12. Bounce your energy away at @bounceincindia 🏀
13. Watch a magical candlelight concert @candlelight.concerts 🕯️
14. Visit the National Museum of Indian Cinema 🎬
15. Laser tag battles at @whatthefunindia 🔫

Have more ideas? Comment below 👇🏼
Summer doesn’t have to be boring when you’ve got these to explore! Save & share this, and follow @mahekpundir for more experiences around the city ✨

latestPosts.caption:
No more Cab Scams in Goa!

Cab monopoly is so common in Goa, better be safe than sorry! Here are some tips:

1️⃣ Ask Terms in Advance – Always clarify rates, hours, and KM limits before confirming the ride.
2️⃣ Never Pay Upfront – Pay only after the ride or as per discussed milestones.
3️⃣ Track Time & Distance – Note the starting KM and use Google Maps to track the route.
4️⃣ Keep Valuables With You – Don’t leave passports, jewelry, or cash in the cab.
5️⃣ Get Everything in Writing – Confirm details via WhatsApp or email for safety.
6️⃣ Use Referred Drivers – Book cabs recommended by someone you trust.
7️⃣ Try GoaMiles – A decent app option for prime areas (though limited in remote spots).
8️⃣ Hope for Ola/Uber Soon – Buzz says they *might* be allowed—fingers crossed for safer, regulated rides! 🤞

Share this with someone planning Goa, and follow me for more travel tips and updates!
